text: Piet Bannenberg (3 January 1911 - 6 March 2002) was a Dutch swimmer. He competed in the men's 4 × 200 metre freestyle relay event at the 1928 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1911 births Category:2002 deaths Category:Dutch male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of the Netherlands Category:Swimmers at the 1928 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Amsterdam Category:Male freestyle swimmers
